summary: okay but... i really do think that their posting of that video today was completely intentional. it’s no coincidence that only...
body: okay but… i really do think that their posting of that video today was completely intentional. it’s no coincidence that only FOUR days after the most open video they’ve ever released and shortly before spooky week, they put out an EXTREMELY gay video on the anniversary of the day they first met. in fact, they’ve done this the last two years. in 2016, they put out the tour bus tour video (which, might i remind you all, caused MASSES of Gay Panic). last year, in 2017, they released truth bombs. the real truth bomb: they don’t like talking about october 19th. i’ve already said today that i think there’s a reason they don’t acknowledge it publicly. i think it’s one of those things that they just want to be special for the two of them. i think these videos are just their way of celebrating publicly. seven years later, we’re on tour. eight years later, we’re creating a board game. nine years later, we’re more open than ever. they may not talk explicitly about october 19th in public, but they speak to us about it in volumes.

summary: I think the reason dnp were fawning over eachother so much in this video was because this game really encapsulates... them. They...
body: I think the reason dnp were fawning over eachother so much in this video was because this game really encapsulates… them. They met because of youtube. EDITING TIPS FFS. And a game about clickbaiting, funny titles, creative media and all the things they originally bonded over and now built an empire around is so perfect for them. The video has that “I love how your mind works” energy. That 2009 energy. And then to release it on today of all days… it might have that flashy clickbait joke façade but it’s a really appropriate and symbolic video. In this essay I will…
